verbose_text: Addition of higher doses of aPCC (250, 500, and 1,000 mU/mL) resulted in fibrin aggregation levels similar or higher than that in PNP (XREF_TABLE, OCP parameter), while the fibrin aggregation onset was delayed significantly when lower doses (25 and 50 mU/mL) were used, thus making the calculation of all OHP assay parameters impossible.
